snippet.textDisplay: as a long time uzi fan that has been binging on leaks for the past 3 years, this shit was really a let down. i think what many of the dickriders seem to miss is that yes, the album is not  t r a s h, it wasnt unbearable like the big day or anything, but god damn was it disappointing. like i understand if yall may like some of the songs on here, i did too, but it just wasnt innovative or genre pushing like i really thought it would be. i have listened to this album three times now and its just not the same ear crack as his earlier tapes were. the hooks, the melodies, his vocal inflections were all instantly ear catching and great. he always offered something new, and unfortunately for three years worth of hype this shit just fell painfully short, and you can like the album and all, whatever, but i sincerely think youre lying to yourself in thinking uzi did anything new or lived up to not only the hype but just his general expectations with this album. theres a reason why artists like kendrick can also take a three year break but at least we know that the man is gonna challenge and entertain us; eternal atake couldve easily been released in 2018 🤷‍♂️

snippet.textDisplay: Once again, bald man does not understand Lil Uzi Vert. I’m sorry it doesn’t register with you old man, but that doesn’t mean you have to pretend like you know what you’re saying. You keep looking for things in his albums that were never meant to be there. Let me try to break down what Uzi’s music is about, though it’s not easy to. He’s not your run of the mill lyrical rapper that’s gonna rap to you about relatable things and concepts which is what you are always so desperately grasping for. Uzi is a damn free spirit who takes an instrumental and pastes his RAW present feelings and flow onto it. Hes not out here making the most clever wordplay, but that’s OBVIOUS, it’s clear that’s not really what hes going for. Uzis music makes his fans feel GOOD. He takes them away from the everyday monotony and raises and uplifts them, he will take an instrument to a level you’ve never heard before, this man will switch flows easily 10 times in one song. That is not easy to do, in fact he’s the only rapper out there who can switch up flows so flawlessly, over and over again. Tracks like Baby Pluto and Celebration station for example, the range of his tone and flows are ridiculous. Just when you think he can’t switch it up any better, there he goes again. Uzi isn’t making music for guys like you to sit down and scratch your chin about, just have some damn fun with it. Dance, feel, let fucking loose
